v0.26.03

General Usage:
Added text on-screen to indicate when a game isn't recognised

Overhauled settings, more training mode settings are saved.
Renamed config files from config.lua to [ROM].config for clarity.
Two more config files have been added. colour.config and generalsettings.config
Both of these files are saved in config/ and their settings transfer between games.
These files can be freely deleted and regenerated fresh, or dropped into another copy of the training mode to share settings.
Config files now disregard default settings when saving to reduce filesize.

Respaced GUI buttons for centre-alignment.
Many popups and scrolling options have also been respaced to be more intuitive.
Buttons are now navigated using cardinal directions, rather than stepping through the buttons on the page.
'Back' has a history of ten pages now, and pressing 'Back' with no history closes the GUI

Added colour to many GUI elements.
Added a colour editor to change those colours, new colours are stored in colour.config

Buttons now properly display whether they can be hotkeyed or if info is associated with them at the bottom of the screen.
Added more buttons for hotkeying, see 'Recording Menu' -> 'Extra Buttons' and 

Added a reset to default ('DFLT') button for each setting

Rearranged some GUI elements to hopefully be more intuitive

'0' no longer displays when P2 is in hitstun.
Updated the combo logic to be more accurate

Savestates:
Savestates now save in their game directory and are named after their game

HUD:
Now navigated using cardinal directions.
Each HUD Element will has a 'DFLT' button

When control is swapped between P1 and P2, it visibly displays.

Replays:
The GUI display of the statuses of the slots and which is being played back by what has been updated to hopefully be more clear.
Reworked some of the buttons to be more clear on

Saved Replays not save with the replay settings.
Replays are saved as [ROM].replaypack.
Loaded Replays validate that the ROM name is the same.

Replays on loop with a max delay set randomise their delay now

LUA Hotkeys:
The LUA hotkeys have been re-done.
1 -> Replay the selected Slot, if the GUI is open, it instead operates the button.
2 -> Starts recording into the selected Slot, if the GUI is open, it instead moves the selection to the next button.
3 -> Swaps the inputs between P1 and P2, if the GUI is open, it instead displays the button info (if applicable).
4 -> Toggles the GUI On or Off.
5 -> Opens Mission addon.
9 -> Reloads GUI.

Addon:
The addon system was introduced.
Missions were previously a ssf2xjr1-specific feature, but are now global (LUA key 5)
A Rewind script was ported for watching replays from fightcade (still buggy!)
A Memory Watch script was ported to help find memory values (DEBUG mode only!)

