Notes for developers:
This version comes with several major reworks of functionality.
Be warned that many of the global function signatures have changed. e.g. CIG -> changePageAndSelection
New values exposed for writing guipages, see interactivegui.boxxhalflength, LETTER_WIDTH etc.
Renamed some game paths to better match ROM names.
Settings no longer save in DEBUG mode (settings are still loaded, however).
New system of adding custom config settings for saving.
New system for adding custom HUD Elements.
Added a 'text item' for drawing text to the screen for a number of frames, see addTextItem()
Added functions to allow game luas to regenerate constants for the training mode.
i.e. Picking a new character that has a different max health from the previous character can now be handled.
Examine sfiii3.lua and its guipages.lua to see these new option in action, alongside the new colour system and spacing buttons.


